---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Espionage — Spy Terms That Score Big"
  description="Spy and espionage words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. CRYPTIC (14pts), CIPHER (13pts), STEALTH (10pts). Intelligence vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble spy words, cryptic scrabble points, cipher scrabble, stealth scrabble, espionage terms scrabble, intelligence words scrabble, spy vocabulary scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Espionage — Spy Terms That Score Big","description":"Spy and espionage words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. CRYPTIC (14pts), CIPHER (13pts), STEALTH (10pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-espionage"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is CRYPTIC a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! CRYPTIC scores 14 points (C=3, R=1, Y=4, P=3, T=1, I=1, C=3) in Scrabble. It means having a hidden or ambiguous meaning. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play CIPHER in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. CIPHER scores 13 points (C=3, I=1, P=3, H=4, E=1, R=1). It refers to a secret code or a method of encoding messages. A strong 6-letter play."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is STEALTH valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! STEALTH scores 10 points (S=1, T=1, E=1, A=1, L=1, T=1, H=4) as a 7-letter word. It's a bingo candidate worth 10 base points plus the 50-point bonus."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Espionage — Spy Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The shadowy world of espionage provides a surprising arsenal of high-scoring Scrabble words. From coded messages to covert operations, spy terminology is packed with valuable letters like Y, P, H, and C that can transform your rack into intelligence gold.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CRYPTIC</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CIPHER</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">STEALTH</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DECRYPT</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Spy Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">CRYPTIC — 14 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">C=3, R=1, Y=4, P=3, T=1, I=1, C=3 · 7 letters · Bingo candidate</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Having a hidden or ambiguous meaning. CRYPTIC is a 7-letter bingo candidate worth 14 points plus the 50-point bonus. The Y=4, P=3, and double C=3 give it serious firepower.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔐 CIPHER</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · C=3, I=1, P=3, H=4, E=1, R=1 · Secret code</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🕵️ STEALTH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · S=1, T=1, E=1, A=1, L=1, T=1, H=4 · Bingo candidate</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🗝️ DECRYPT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 pts · D=2, E=1, C=3, R=1, Y=4, P=3, T=1 · 7 letters</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📡 COVERT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · C=3, O=1, V=4, E=1, R=1, T=1 · Hidden ops</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Intelligence Vocabulary</h2>
      <p>Espionage vocabulary provides strong mid-range options from relatively common tiles:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AGENT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SLEEPER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MOLE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SHADOW</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SPYING</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Espionage Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CRYPTIC is your bingo target:</span> At exactly 7 letters, CRYPTIC (14pts + 50 bonus = 64pts) needs no hooks. When you see C, R, Y, P, T, I, C on your rack — play it immediately.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CIPHER leverages H and P together:</span> H=4 and P=3 combine with C=3 for 13 points from 6 tiles. Strong return per tile played.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SHADOW uses the H tile well:</span> At 13 points with H=4 and W=4, SHADOW scores high from mostly common tiles. Place the H on a double-letter square for 17 points.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Espionage words are <span class="text-white font-medium">C-tile and Y-tile specialists</span>. CRYPTIC, CIPHER, COVERT, and DECRYPT all use C=3 effectively. When you draw C and Y together, think spy — the vocabulary delivers consistent 10+ point plays.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-detective/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Detective Fiction</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-technology/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Technology</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-science/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Science</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid spy word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
